<HEADLINE> Iran Beats China 4-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHERAN, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Iran trounced China 4-1 Friday
in a World Cup qualifying Asian Group A match, hugely boosting its
World Cup final hopes.
</P>
<P>
The Iranians opened the accounting just two minutes into the
match through a long drive from midfielder Alireza
Mansouriyan. The host made it 2-0 by Ali Asghar Modir Rousta, just
before halftime.
</P>
<P>
Iran never let it up in the second half with Bundasliga
defender Karim Bagheri driving home a deflected goal. Another
Bundasliga player, striker Ali Daie put the result beyond the
doubt by netting the last Iranian goal in the 27th minute.
</P>
<P>
China scored a consolation goal by Mao Yijun in the 42th minute.
</P>
<P>
The home victory rewards Iran 11 points with three wins and two
draws, standing atop in the group. China collects seven points
with a record of 2-1-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
