<HEADLINE> Swedish Businesses Eager to Invest in Pakistan: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Swedish Secretary of
Trade Yvonne Gustafsson said here today Pakistan can be a big
market for her country's investors "who are eager to invest here."
</P>
<P>
There is a great potential for mutually-beneficial cooperation
between Pakistan and Sweden in the fields of industry, science and
technology, said Gustafsson at a reception hosted by Swedish
Ambassador Nils Rosenberg.
</P>
<P>
Gustafsson, who is currently heading a high profile nine-member
trade and industry delegation to Pakistan, has earlier met with
Pakistani ministers for finance, commerce and communication.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's economy has bright prospects, once it starts picking
up, Gustafasson said. "But from experience in our country five
years back, I can say Pakistan needs to follow the economic
reforms diligently for that stage."
</P>
<P>
"The Swedish businessmen have shown keen interest in exploiting
the market potential that Pakistan offers and I am sure this visit
will bring more investment," she said.
</P>
<P>
Swedish Ambassador Rosenberg said the visit of the Swedish
secretary of trade will be rewarding in enhancing business
activities as well as strengthening the bilateral relations.
</P>
</TEXT>
