<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Egyptian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Egyptian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Al-Ahram:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Chairman of the General Investment Authority
Ibrahim Fawzi said it had been decided to start carrying out the
biggest project for producing steel foil with Egyptian-Italian
joint investments worth more than 600 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Al-Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Sophisticated arms and equipment will be used for the first
time in the "Bright Star" war games which started on October 9 and
will last until late this month in Egypt. The maneuvers also
involve the U.S., Britain, France, Italy, the United Arab Emirates
and Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Al-Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa Thursday voiced
pessimism over the future of the deadlocked Middle East peace
process, warning anew that Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu's hardline policies threaten the peace moves in the
Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- The U.N. Special Committee in charge of dismantling Iraqi
mass-destruction weapons chief Richard Butler said Iraq has warned
the U.N. it would end cooperating with U.N. arms inspectors if
further sanctions are imposed by the Security Council. 
</P>
