<HEADLINE> Santoro Moves into Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Fabrice Santoro routed fourth
seed Felix Mantilla 6-1, 6-1 after winning 11 consecutive games
Friday to move into the Lyon Grand Prix semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Santoro lost the initial game but raced through the next six to
take the first set. Then he raced to a 5-0 lead in the second set
and won the 66 minute match.
</P>
<P>
In another quarterfinal, Tommy Haas of Germany upset
fifth-seeded Thomas Enqvist of Sweden, 6-3, 6-3 to make his second
semifinal of the year.
</P>
<P>
Later Friday Cedric Pioline faces Mark Philippoussis and
defending champion Yevgeny Kafelnikov takes on Marc Goellner.
</P>
</TEXT>
