<HEADLINE> Four Killed in Jeep-Truck Collision in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Four people were killed and
six others injured seriously when a jeep collided with a truck in
India's Uttar Pradesh today, the Press Trust of India reported.
</P>
<P>
The jeep driver was among the killed, police said.
</P>
<P>
The mishap took place while the victims were on their way from
a religious function. 
</P>
