<HEADLINE> Mongolian Government Survives Sacking Vote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The Mongolian parliament,
the Great Hural, today rejected the proposal by the Mongolian
People's Revolution Party (MPRP) that the government resign.
</P>
<P>
The vote, following two days heated debate in the Great Hural,
was participated in by 73 of the 75 parliament members, and ended
with 47 against and 25 for the motion.
</P>
<P>
During the debate, the ruling Mongolian National Democratic
Party argued that the country's economy had started to show
improvements, the result of the government's economic policies.
</P>
<P>
Mongolian President Nachagyn Bagabandy called on the
parliament to give the government a chance to correct its
mistakes. Dismissing the government was not the only way to solve
the country's problems, he said.
</P>
<P>
On October 4, MPRP members of the parliament submitted a draft
proposal to the Great Hural urging the government to resign on
grounds of corruption and because of a sluggish economy.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-three of the country's 75 parliamentarians, mainly from
the MPRP, signed the proposal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
