<HEADLINE> Mugabe to Attend CHOGM Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean president Robert
Mugabe leaves Harare on Monday for Edinburgh, Scotland, to attend
the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting (CHOGM), the
Ministry of Foreign Affairs said today.
</P>
<P>
This year's heads of government meeting, scheduled to take
place between October 24 and 27, would for the first time focus
on economic rather than political issues under the theme "Trade,
Investment and Development -- the Road to Commonwealth
Prosperity", the ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"The meeting will also provide an opportunity to share ideas
on how the commonwealth can contribute to the sustainable
development of its member governments and to the economic
globalisation process," the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The problems of Cyprus, Nigeria, Sierra Leone and Gambia would
be high on the agenda with heads of government reviewing
recommendations from the Commonwealth Ministerial Action Group
(CMAG).
</P>
<P>
The CMAG was, through the Harare declaration, asked to monitor
good governance, human rights and democracy in member nations.
</P>
<P>
The commonwealth would also consider membership applications
from Rwanda and Yemen as well as the expression of interest in
joining the body from the Palestine national authority.
</P>
<P>
While in Edinburgh, Mugabe was also expected to hold talks
with British Prime Minister Tony Blair on a number of bilateral
and international issues, including the land issue.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe and his delegation were expected back home on October
29, the ministry said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
