<HEADLINE> Becker, Draper into Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Germany's former world number
one Boris Becker and Australia's Scott Draper qualified for the
semi-finals at the Hong Kong Tennis Championships in Victoria
Park Friday.
</P>
<P>
They joined French Open champion Gustavo Kuerten from Brazil
and Byron Black from Zimbabwe, the two who earned their spots in
the men's singles top four on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In Gold Group's last match Friday, Becker beat Jonathan Stark
of the United States 4-6, 6-4, 6-3 to enter the semi-finals as the
group winner.
</P>
<P>
Becker won over Italian Renzo Furlan 6-7, 6-3, 6-3 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Draper of the Red Group defeated Vincent Spadea of the United
States 6-1, 6-3. This was his second victory in the round-robin
group matches, following his 6-3, 6-2 win over Peter Tramacchi of
Australia on Wednesday. Tramacchi replaced the group's seeded
player Albert Costa from Spain, who quit the event for shoulder
injuries.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Johansson of Sweden beat Justin Gimelstob of the United
States 7-5, 7-5 in Blue Group's final match. The result of the
match came out meaningless as Kuerten had already won the group's
top place with two consecutive wins.
</P>
<P>
In the semi-finals on Saturday, Kuerten meets Black and Becker
takes on Draper.
</P>
<P>
The final is set for Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
