<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU to Sponsor Clearing of Minefields in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Tenders for the 96 million U.S.
Dollars landmine clearing project have been invited to clear the
northeastern areas of Zimbabwe of deadly mines planted during the
war of liberation along border areas, the Zimbabwe News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The tender invitation says the demining would be sponsored by
the European Union.
</P>
<P>
The clearing of the minefields would create valuable land for
agriculture to adjacent rural areas.
</P>
<P>
There are seven minefields about 750 kilometers mostly along
the border areas.
</P>
<P>
Communities in the border areas of Zimbabwe have lived in fear
since before independence in 1980 because of the danger of mines.
</P>
<P>
The mines have killed or maimed unsuspecting civilians who
mistook them for toys or touched them for other reasons.
</P>
<P>
The clearing of the mines comes in the wake of the a worldwide
campaign to ban the manufacturing and sale of anti-personnel
mines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
