<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dread El Nino Arrives in Zimbabwe: Expert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 17 (Xinhua) -- A Zimbabwean climate expert
confirmed today that the dread El Nino weather phenomenon had
finally arrived in the country.
</P>
<P>
Coordinator of climate change in the Ministry of Mines,
Environment and Tourism Todd Ngara said the unusual cold spell
and spring rains being experienced in the country are typical El
Nino patterns.
</P>
<P>
He said the current phenomenon would pass on towards December,
resulting in high temperatures, sporadic and little rains.
</P>
<P>
Ngara, however said the country may not experience drought
conditions, but the probability is "very" high.
</P>
<P>
In 1991/92, the country experienced the worst drought in
living memory due to the El Nino, which caused heavy flooding in
northern pacific countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
