<DOCNO> XIE19971018.0024 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Rwandan PM Sued by U.N. Tribunal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The indictments of former
Rwandan Prime Minister Jean Kambanda has been confirmed, said a
news release issued today by the U.N. International Criminal
Tribunal for Rwanda based in Arusha, northern Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Tribunal Judge Yakov Ostrovsky said on Thursday that Kambanda
was charged with six counts -- genocide, conspiracy to commit
genocide, direct and public incitement to commit genocide,
complicity in genocide, and crimes against humanity.
</P>
<P>
Kambanda, born in 1955 in Gishamvu commune in Rwanda, was said
to have directly and publicly incited Rwandans to commit acts of
violence, causing serious bloody harm to Tutsis and moderate
Hutus.
</P>
<P>
He was also accused of having distributed arms and ammunition
for use in committing the massacres in 1994.
</P>
<P>
He was arrested in Kenya last July during a Nairobi-Kigali
joint operation and now is detained in Arusha. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
