<HEADLINE> Some Diet Members Pay Homage at Yasukuni Shrine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Some members of the Japanese
Parliament, the Diet, today paid a collective homage at the
Yasukuni Shrine, the Japanese media reported.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 103 Diet members who paid homage at the shrine, 66
came from the House of Representatives and 37 from the House of
Councillors.
</P>
<P>
Among the remains in the Yasukuni Shrine are 13 top World War
II criminals. Paying homage at the shrine by Japanese officials is
strongly opposed by the people of Asian countries. 
