<HEADLINE> Davenport Advances in semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, Oct 17 (Xinhua) -- Lindsay Davenport moved into the
semifinals of the European indoor championships, beating Venus
Williams 6-0, 6-4 in Zurich on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The two Americans took just 55 minutes to finish the match with
fourth seed Davenport won over her teenage compatriot Williams.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, world number six, made very few mistakes,
particularly in the first set when she broke her 26th ranked
opponent three times.
</P>
<P>
In the second set Williams began to show signs of life when she
broke Davenport to level at 1-1. But Davenport refused to
relinquish control, recording the decisive break at 5-4 then
serving out the match to reach the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Nathalie Tauziat of France came back from a set down to book
her place in the semifinals with a 4-6, 6-1, 7-5 win over
Belgium's Sabine Applemans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
