<HEADLINE> OAU Commits to Strengthening African-Chinese Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Salim Ahmed Salim,
secretary general of the Organization of African Unity (OAU),
today expressed his organization's commitment to strengthening
the relations between Africa and China.
</P>
<P>
He told visiting Chinese Vice-minister of Foreign Affairs Tian
Zengpei that a stronger and unified China is very important to
Africa, developing countries and the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Salim recalled that China has made great contributions to both
African liberation struggle and African development, saying that
African countries expressed their thanks for China's support and
help.
</P>
<P>
The OAU secretary general said, the important address made by
Chinese President Jiang Zemin to the OAU when he visited here
last year reaffirmed China's continuing development of its
relations with Africa and Chinese principles for developing
relations with African countries.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his admiration to Chinese leaders, the Chinese
government and the Chinese people for their support and
contributions to Africa.
</P>
<P>
He said, the important visits to Africa by Chinese President
Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng have strengthened the relations
between Africa and China and promoted the understanding between
African peoples and Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Before the meeting, the Chinese vice foreign minister, on
behalf of the Chinese government, donated 15 computers to the
OAU.
</P>
<P>
Tian and his six-member delegation arrived here on Thursday
for a three-day working visit to Ethiopia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
