<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Urges Renewed Determination to Combat Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 17 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General
Kofi Annan today called upon international society to work
together more closely and at all levels of the United Nations to
spearhead the war against poverty.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion of the International Day for the
Eradication of Poverty, the Secretary-General said that some
individuals were enjoying wealth on a scale previously unimagined.
Yet, victims of poverty still endured intolerable froms of
deprivation. They continued to be marginalized and excluded. The
International Day for the Eradication of Poverty remained us world
of the road we had yet to travel and the battles we had yet to
win.
</P>
<P>
The UN chief said the relative incidence of poverty had
declined somewhat. But the number of the world's poor had risen
considerably. Almost one quarter of the world's population still
lived in a state of poverty.
</P>
<P>
Annan said that poverty had always been a prime concern in the
work of the United Nations. In recent years, the fight against
poverty had been the subject of heightened attention. The
eradication of poverty had also become the common thread of major
United Nations conferences of the 1990s, especially the world
summit for social development.
</P>
<P>
He said eradication of poverty required enhanced economic
growth and employment opportunities. The causes of poverty should
also be addressed in the context of sectoral strategies, such as
the environment, food security, population, migration, health,
shelter, human resources development, fresh water and rural
development.
</P>
<P>
Annan stressed that there was no shortage of strategies and
plans, analyses and statistics, approaches and measures. What we
needed was a renewed determination and willingness to bring all
sectors together in one unstinting effort. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
