<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angolan National Energy Meeting Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- An Angolan national energy
policy meeting ended here today, urging the setting up of an
inter-ministry special commission to formulate national energy
policy for the approval by the government.
</P>
<P>
A document, approved at the meeting from Tuesday to Friday
which was attended by more than 100 delegates, said that the
special commission should include ministries of energy and water,
petroleum, agriculture, geology and mining, communications,
environment, industry and other government departments.
</P>
<P>
The inter-ministry commission should listen to views and
suggestions from all walks of life.
</P>
<P>
The delegates agreed that the national energy policy to be
formulated should ensure long-term and reliable supply of energy
for the Angolans, reasonable and effective use of energy
resources and proper portection of environment at the same time.
</P>
<P>
Angolan Minister of Energy and Water Joao Saraiva said that
the closing ceremony of the meeting that Angola, rich in energy
resources, should exploit energy resources reasonably, both to
promote economic development and to protect environment.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of Norway, Brazil, South Africa, Mozambique
Namibia and Tanzania were also present at the meeting at the
invitation of Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
