<HEADLINE> Mechanical Defects Cause Bus Accident in Quebec </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Mechanical defects are to blame
for the fatal bus accident that killed 43 people in the Canadian
province of Quebec earlier this week, reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Inspectors of the wreckage have concluded that the tour bus had
certain mechanical problems, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Forty-three people were killed and five seriously injured in
the worst road accident in the history of Canada on October 13.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at 2:15 p.m. on Highway 138, about 100
kilometers northeast of Quebec city.
</P>
<P>
It happened on a steep road in the mountainous Charlevoix
region. The bus failed to negotiate a sharp turn and went into a
ravine.
</P>
<P>
Road conditions were reported to be dry and weather sunny.
</P>
</TEXT>
