<HEADLINE> Iraq's Population Hit 22 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Iraq's population is now
22,017,983, Iraqi Higher Commission for General Census (HCGC)
announced today.
</P>
<P>
The HCGC said in a statement that the number of the males hits
10,940,764, representing 49.7 percent of the whole population and
that of females hits 11,077,219.
</P>
<P>
The last census in Iraq in 1987 showed the Iraqi population was
16,278,316.
</P>
<P>
Director of the Central Authority for Census and Secretary of
the HCGC Adnad Shihab pointed out that the process of the census,
the eighth one of the country and the first of its kind since the
1991 Gulf War, was well-run.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Iraqi citizens responded positively to the
census staff and offered them all informations they need. No
troubles took place during the process.
</P>
<P>
Some 159,000 government officials went door-to-door Thursday to
help fill in the census forms distributed to urban and rural areas
throughout the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
