<HEADLINE> UN S.Leone Sanction Committee Elects New Head </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's permanent representative to
the United Nations, Hans Dahlgren, has been elected chairman of the
committee set up by the Security Council to supervise and implement
the sanctions on Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The committee also elected the envoys of Kenya and Costa Rica as
vice-chairmen, the News Agency of Nigeria reported today.
</P>
<P>
The committee comprising all 15 members of the Security Council is
to recommend guidelines to facilitate the implementation of the
sanctions, liaise with ECOWAS on the sanctions and approve petroleum
imports if so requested by ousted President Ahmed Tejan Kabbah's
government or the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The council announced Wednesday last week to impose oil and arms
embargo as well as travel restrictions on the military junta in Sierra
Leone for an early restoration of Kabbah's legitimate government
toppled in a coup in May this year.
</P>
<P>
It has also authorized the Economic Community of West African
States (ECOWAS) to enforce the measures through its peacekeeping force
known as ECOMOG. 
</P>
</TEXT>
