<HEADLINE> Chinese Cultural Days Opened in Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The Days of the Chinese Culture
opened here this evening at the Moscowcky Little Theater after a
40-year break of the cultural exchange between China and Russia.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony Russian Minister of Culture Nataliya
Dementieva described the Chinese cultural days as "a great event in
the life of our two countries." The cultural action will make the
fruitful cooperation between Russia and China more active, she
emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Deputy Minister of Culture Men Xiaosi in her speech
said that this was the most large-scale cultural exchange activity
in relations between the two countries, to which China attached
importance. In accordance with the agreement signed by the two
sides in July last year, the Russian Cultural Days would open in
Beijing next year. "We will greet the Russian days in Beijing,"
she said.
</P>
<P>
The opening ceremony was highlighted by the brilliant
performances of Beijing opera and the Chinese national orchestra,
which drew loud applause from the audience.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Cultural Days include the exhibition
"Masterpieces of national Chinese Go-Hua arts of the 20th
century", the exhibition of photographs and a week of Chinese
movies. Besides, the Chinese artists will perform Beijing opera,
acrobatics, national music, songs and dances.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese artists will tour the cities of St. Petersburg,
Nizhni Novgorod, Vladimir and Novosibirsk, and then officially
closed the days of Chinese culture in the Far Eastern city of
Khabarovsk on October 26. 
</P>
</TEXT>
