<HEADLINE> US Treasury Building Evacuated in Moving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Treasury's main
building, which is adjacent to the White House, was evacuated for
more than two hours today after a suspicious package was found.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms
said later that the package had been removed, but he said it was
too early to know if it contained an explosive.
</P>
<P>
The evacuation involved some 2,000 employees who work in the
building. They were moved to nearby streets when a police official
dressed in heavy protective clothing and helmet removed the
package from the building and placed it in a van.
</P>
<P>
Police cordoned off several streets near the Treasury when the
incident began shortly after noon, causing huge traffic jams in
downtown Washington.
</P>
<P>
The Treasury building was damaged last year in a fire that
started accidentally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
