<HEADLINE> First Film Festival in South Asia to Be Held in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 18 (Xinhua) -- A documentary film festival
named Film South Asia '97, the first in this region, is to be held
here on October 25-28, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 45 documentaries from India, Pakistan, Bangladesh,
Sri Lanka and Nepal will be screened during the festival organized
by the Kathmandu-based regional magazine Himal South Asia.
</P>
<P>
The best film will be awarded a prize of 2,500 U.S. dollars,
while the second and third prizes carry a purse of 1,500 dollars
and 1,000 dollars respectively, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The organizer said the festival aims to offer an opportunity
for professionals and enthusiasts from the region to gather
together and establish working relationship for the cause of
documentary filmmaking.
</P>
<P>
Two workshops on "Trends in Documentary Filmmaking in South
Asia" and "Documentaries in the Age of Satellite Television" will
also be held during the festival, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
The festival will be a biennial event, the organizer said.
</P>
