<HEADLINE> Russia Greets Potential in Lithuania Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Russia and Lithuania share a
great potential in developing trade with each other, Russian
Deputy Prime Minister Valery Serov said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the Interfax news agency after the first meeting of
the Russia-Lithuania committee on trade, technology and culture
cooperation, Serov emphasized that Lithuania is now Russia's major
trade partner in the Baltic region.
</P>
<P>
Serov, who is a chairman of the inter-governmental organization
of Russia and Lithuania, said the bilateral trade between the two
countries is expected to reach 1.7 billion U.S. dollars in 1997,
an increase of 33 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
If the momentum continued, there would further increases of
trade volumes, he said.
</P>
<P>
Serov said Russia, as the legitimate inheritor of the former
Soviet Union, would solve debt problems through methods that were
also applied to other former Soviet Union's republics. 
</P>
