<DOCNO> XIE19971018.0063 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuerten, Black Qualify for HK Championships Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's French Open champion
Gustavo Kuerten and Zimbabwe's Byron Black won berths in the final
of the 1997 Marlboro Tennis Championships in Victoria Park on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Kuerten beat Australian Scott Draper 6-3, 6-4 and Black took
the other final berth of the 722,500 U.S. dollar event by edging
Germany's former world number one Boris Becker 7-6 (7-3), 6-7
(6-8), 6-4.
</P>
<P>
As an unseeded 21-year-old right-hander, Kuerten took the crown
of this year's French Open by beating Spain's Sergi Bruguera in
straight sets.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian took an upper hand in the semi-final against
Draper Saturday, when he broke service three times and unleashed
seven Aces in the one-hour-three-minute match.
</P>
<P>
Becker, now 29 and ranked 22nd in the world, has been taken as
one of the greatest singles player in the world. Long-standing
injuries and age took the toll as he looked exhausted in the third
and final set.
</P>
<P>
Black, who won the doubles title with Canadian Grant Connell at
last year's Marlboro championships here, is ranked 61st in the
world. His highest singles ranking is 22nd in April last year.
</P>
<P>
Becker and Black had met twice before and both of the 1995
matches ended in favor of the German.
</P>
<P>
Both Becker and Black held their service in the opening
set. Becker made seven Aces while making numerous unforced errors,
which cost him the set 7-6 (7-3).
</P>
<P>
Becker improved his service and scored nine Aces in the second
set and, with successful volleys, he won the set 7-6 (8-6) to
level with the Zimbabwe ace.
</P>
<P>
Black gradually took the initiative in the third set after
breaking Becker's service in the opening game and he never gave up
the lead to win the set 6-4 and the match of two hours and eleven
minutes.
</P>
<P>
The championships final is set for Sunday afternoon. Kuerten
and Black split honors in their two previous meetings, in the ATP
hard court events in Memphis and Indian Wells, earlier this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
