<HEADLINE> Pakistan Ready for U.S. Mediation on Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan is ready for a
mediation initiative from the United States and other countries to
achieve a fair solution to the Kashmir dispute, a Foreign Office
spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman made the remarks when responding at a news
briefing to a question about U.S. mediation on the Kashmir dispute
between Pakistan and India.
</P>
<P>
He said: "Pakistan is ready for whatever initiative that will
bring a peaceful, just and fair solution to the problem."
</P>
<P>
"The U.S. is a friend of India; the U.S. is a friend of
Pakistan; there are other friends. Let the friends play a certain
role, why not, after all."
</P>
<P>
The spokesman emphasized that in the past Pakistan and India
had solved other issues through mediation and arbitration.
</P>
<P>
The Kashmir dispute followed the 1947 division of India into
India and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan demanded that the sovereignty of the region be decided
in accordance with related United Nations resolutions or by other
countries' mediation.
</P>
<P>
But India rejected mediation by a third country and said that
a solution should be reached through bilateral negotiations.
</P>
</TEXT>
