<HEADLINE> Zambian Government Concerned With Child Abuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lusaka, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Zambian vice president Godfrey
Miyanda said here today that the government is concerned with the
high rate of child abuse and is reviewing the laws to that
effect.
</P>
<P>
While officiating a youth rally for world aids campaign he
said the laws alone cannot help change the present situation and
called on youths to be realistic and understand the situation.
</P>
<P>
He said youths sould abstain from pre-marital sex and should
also teach others about its dangers.
</P>
<P>
The youths are the seed of this population to ensure
continuity of life but many young people today tend to make wrong
decisions about their lives due to ignorance, the vice president
said.
</P>
<P>
The function which drew participants from primary schools and
youth organizations of the country is meant to campaign for the
forthcoming World AIDS Day which falls on December the first.
</P>
<P>
Luzia Wetzel, Zambia coordinator of the Youth Alive Club,
urged parents to protect children against sexual abuse, saying
that they are innocent and look up to parents for protection.
</P>
<P>
The Youth Alive Club is the organizer of the rally. 
</P>
