<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 18 (Xinhua) -- World Bank President James D.
Wolfensohn today arrived in Lahore, capital of Pakistan's eastern
Punjab province, on his 5-day visit to the country, official
sources said.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Pakistan, the 64-year-old Wolfensohn, who is
heading a 7-member delegation, will meet Pakistani President
Farooq Leghari, Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif and other senior
officials, the sources said.
</P>
