other development projects, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's relationship with the World Bank Group started in
1952. To date, the World Bank has approved 88 loans and 137
credits for Pakistan with a nominal loan value amounting to 11.5
billion U.S. dollars in some 231 operations, according to the
World Bank statistics.  
