<HEADLINE> African Defense Chiefs to Meet in Harare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Chiefs of defense staff of the
OAU will meet in Harare next Friday to reflect on the continent's
present and future peacekeeping initiatives since the launch in
1993 of the Mechanism for Conflict Prevention, Management and
Resolution in Africa.
</P>
<P>
A statement from Zimbabwean defense forces headquarters today
said that host president and OAU chairman Robert Mugabe is
expected to open the three-day meeting while the continental
body's Secretary-general Salim Ahmed Salim will deliver the
keynote address.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe and Salim will highlight the need for Africa to resolve
the problem of endemic military coups, secessionism, genocide and
many other ills that bedevil the continent, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
"Because the issues at hand are crucial and very topical, the
general secretariat of the OAU decided that all member states
should be invited. Thus, all the 53 member states will be
expected to be represented," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
"Africa has awakened to the message that it must be seen to be
taking the lead in resolving African problems," the statement
said. 
</P>
