<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Able to Produce Missile Launching Boats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Iran today claimed that it is
capable of designing and producing small missile launching boats
and moving closer to building small tactical submarines.
</P>
<P>
Admiral Ali Akbar Ahmadian said the Islamic Revolutionary Guard
Corps (IRGC) naval force has made strides toward self-sufficiency
by obtaining up-to-date knowledge in designing, upgrading and
manufacturing modern vessels.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the commander of
the IRGC naval force made the statement at the "Piroozi (Victory)
8" exercises zone near the southern port city of Bushehr.
</P>
<P>
"The new missile launching boats would be deployed in the next
joint military exercises code-named "Piroozi 9," he was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The admiral said that apart from designing and manufacturing
small missile launching boats, considerable progress has been made
in producing small tactical submarines as well.
</P>
<P>
He said that the missile system had turned Iran into the
strongest missile power in the region and the upgraded missile
systems of his force have been successfully tested in the
exercises from October 11 to 17 that hypothesized every condition
of a modern missile warfare.
</P>
<P>
He said the drilling troops carried out joint missions using
small missile launching boats and IRGC missile sites with complete
success.
</P>
<P>
He added that the shifting of missile sites, radar and modern
communications tests, air and missile launching operations,
expanding missile sites and testing of upgraded missile systems
were included in the exercises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
