<HEADLINE> Li Lanqing Inspects Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing, in a
trip to the Inner Mongolian Autonomous Region last week, said that
areas inhabited by ethnic minority people need to develop their
economy through science and education.
</P>
<P>
"The ethnic minority areas should speed up reforms and
opening-up under the guidance of Deng Xiaoping Theory, under the
leadership of the Communist Party of China Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at the core," said Li, who is also a Standing
Committee member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of
China Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The region has made great social and economic progress in the
past several years, and that maintaining sound economic
development and social stability in the Inner Mongolian Autonomous
Region is vital to China's development and stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li visited some large state-owned enterprises and local
universities in the company of Uliji, deputy secretary of the CPC
Inner Mongolia Regional Committee and chairman of the Inner
Mongolian Autonomous Region government, and others.
</P>
<P>
He also visited homes of some local teachers and citizens, and
expressed his concern for educational development and the living
conditions of teachers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
