<HEADLINE> Chinese Geophysical Society Marks 50th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Geophysical Society
(CGS) celebrated its 50th Anniversary today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Guangya, vice-chairman of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, and president
of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, attended the celebration.
</P>
<P>
CGS director, Liu Guangding, spoke about the great achievements
of the CGS in the past half century in the researches on energy
and water resources, environmental protection, engineering, and
disaster forecasts.
</P>
<P>
He said that CGS will explore for better mines over the next
three years and increase its ocean and outerspace research to meet
the needs of Rapidly-growing national economic construction.
</P>
<P>
CGS was founded in Shanghai in 1947, starting with 26 members,
and now has 1,100, who are engaged in various kinds of scientific
work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
