<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Wins First Time in Group B </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMATY, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan made its first win in
Asian group B World Cup qualifying round when it scored a 3-0
drubbing over United Arab Emirates (UAE) Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan remained the fourth in the group with six points,
but leveled its marks with Japan and just one point away from the
second UAE.
</P>
<P>
Surviving UAE's sporadic counter-attacks in the goalless first
half, Kazakhstan launched a spectacular offensive second-half
game, leading off with Vitaly Sparishev's header in the 55th
minute.
</P>
<P>
Pavel Yevtiyev doubled the lead after 73 minutes and Dmitry
Yurist sealed the victory five minutes later when he stormed the
ball into the net on Emitates defender's mistake.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's other match sees the bottom Uzbekistan meet South
Korea, who atop in the group with 13 points off. 
</P>
