<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Companies Develop Machinery For Medical Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese manufacturers of
machinery used for the pharmaceutical and medical businesses and
other health-care companies have been developing rapidly.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, the industries had 120 billion yuan in
output value.
</P>
<P>
This was one of the important topics at an international
medical and health-care products exhibition that opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Companies from Germany, the United States, Japan, Italy,
Israel, Switzerland, Australia, China, and other countries were
present.
</P>
<P>
China now has 10,000 manufacturers of pharmaceutics and medical
equipment, 1,500 of which are foreign-funded ones, and 15 of the
world's top 20 medical equipment companies have invested in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Local experts say that the market for medical and health-care
products in China is expected to grow steadily with the country's
economic development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
