<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping Theory should Be Applied: Rong Yiren </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Vice-President Rong Yiren, a
non-Communist state leader, has urged people to follow Deng
Xiaoping Theory in all areas.
</P>
<P>
It is important to hold the banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory high
as proposed by the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core, Rong said during an tour
of Wuxi, an industrial city in eastern Jiangsu Province, in the
past two weeks.
</P>
<P>
During his stay, Rong visited villages, enterprises, schools,
and environmental and infrastructure projects. In talks with local
officials, he praised the substantial progress made by Wuxi in
agricultural modernization. He quoted Jiang Zemin as saying that
agriculture should be given top priority in all economic issues.
</P>
<P>
He asked that the problem of too many laborers in the
countryside be dealt with, emphasizing its importance in social
stability.
</P>
<P>
He also paid special attention to environmental protection
measures of the local government dealing with severe pollutions in
Taihu Lake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
