<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Former Chinese Vice-Premier Dies in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Fang Yi, a former vice-premier
of China's State Council, died on October 17 in Beijing at the age
of 81, because of illness.
</P>
<P>
Fang was a battle-hardened Communist fighter, a proletarian
revolutionary, and an outstanding leader in the country's foreign
economic relations and in scientific and technological areas.
</P>
<P>
He also was a former member of the Communist Party of China's
Central Committee Politburo and the CPC Central Committee
Secretariat, and a former vice-chairman of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference National Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
