<HEADLINE> Antigua and Barbuda PM Visits Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister of Antigua and
Barbuda Lester Bird started a two-day private visit to Macao today
following his official trip to China's inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister was greeted by Wang Qiren, director of the
Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch, when he arrived via Zhuhai city,
south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Wang congratulated him on his successful visit to China's
inland areas, and said that bilateral friendship and cooperation
will keep growing since the two countries are both developing
nations and share many things in common.
</P>
<P>
Bird expressed congratulations on China's resumption of
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong this year. He also wished a
smooth transition and handover of power in Macao in 1999.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the prime minister said that he hopes to visit
Macao again after China's resumption of exercise of sovereignty
over Macao, adding that he also hopes to establish a consulate in
Macao in the future.
</P>
<P>
Wang briefed Bird on Macao's transition and the Chinese
government's policy on Macao, saying that a stable transition and
a smooth handover of power will be achieved under the policy of
"one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of China's Premier Li Peng, Bird and his
entourage arrived in Beijing on October 13 for an official
visit. It was his second visit in 13 years.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in China's inland areas, he held talks with Li
Peng and met with other senior Chinese leaders in Beijing, and
visited Shenyang, capital of northeast Liaoning Province, and
Guangzhou, Shenzhen and Zhuhai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
