<HEADLINE> HK Entertainers Plan Theme Restaurants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 18 (Xinhua) -- A group of local
show-business personalities is starting a business to franchise
entertainment-theme restaurants worldwide, a concept similar to
Planet Hollywood, according to local press reports today.
</P>
<P>
The Star East restaurant concept boasts over 40 celebrity
investors including kung fu superstar Jackie Chan, singers Anita
Mui Yim-fong and game-show host Eric Tsang Chi-wei, with singer
Alan Tam Wing-lun serving as chairman.
</P>
<P>
The theme restaurants will serve Asian food to set them apart
from Planet Hollywood invested by a host of Hollywood stars.
</P>
<P>
According to the business's chief financial controller David
Eng, Star East plans to operate about 20 restaurants within two
years through franchise agreements, with start-up cost for each
restaurant estimated at 50 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The first franchised restaurant will be opened on November 1 in
Guangzhou, China's Guangdong Province bordering Hong Kong,
followed by another in Los Angeles next March.
</P>
<P>
Other target places include Hong Kong, Taiwan, Singapore,
Malaysia as well as other major cities in China's interior areas.
</P>
<P>
Eng said the group plans to float their business in three
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
