<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Revised Guideline for HK Banks To Fight Money Laundering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Those who launder money using
shell companies, trusts and nominee accounts in Hong Kong will
have a harder time under a revised guideline issued to banks,
local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The guideline, issued Thursday by the Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA), strengthens the customer identification
requirements when accounts were opened, to find out the real
person behind the corporate facades.
</P>
<P>
The revised guideline, replacing the previous one issued in
July 1993, has taken into account legal changes since then,
including the passage of the Organized and Serious Crimes
Ordinance in 1994 which extends the money laundering offense to
the proceeds of serious crimes other than drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
The new guideline is in line with the latest recommendations of
the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), an international
organization aimed at strengthening global cooperation against
money laundering.
</P>
<P>
"The HKMA takes very seriously the need to prevent use of the
banking system for the purposes of money laundering," said a HKMA
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He added that the guideline will "help to maintain the
reputation and credibility of Hong Kong as an international
financial center."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971018.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia's Prudence Bank Shut Immediately </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Zambia's Prudence Bank will be
shut today with immediate effect due to "unsatisfactory"
compliance with the directives of Bank of Zambia, the country's
central bank, to improve its management.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview with Xinhua, Kabinga Pande, manager
of public relations at Bank of Zambia, confirmed that all branch
offices of Prudence Bank will stop business from now on until
further notice.
</P>
<P>
The central bank has in the meantime taken control and
possession of the bank in order to safeguard the interests of
depositors and the financial system, according to Panda.
</P>
<P>
However, Panda did not give further details about the bank's
mismanagement.
</P>
<P>
Last month, senior management staff and directors at Prudence
Bank were removed from their positions through an order from the
Minister of Finance Ronald Penza following their "unsatisfactory"
compliance with orders given by the central bank to try and
improve operations at the institution.
</P>
<P>
The central bank has appointed one of its senior personnel as
the overall manager of Prudence Bank in order to continue with
its management.
</P>
<P>
Prudence Bank suffered another set-back earlier last month
after its head office went up in flames in an "inferno" which
gutted a 19-floor building in Lusaka's downtown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
