<HEADLINE> Australia, Germany to Vie for Gold Medal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Germany set up a final clash
with Australia in the Champions Trophy men's field hockey Sunday
after defeating Spain 3-2 Saturday in Adelaide, Australia.
</P>
<P>
Germany had to win to progress to the final before the match,
while Spain, on equal points with the Germans but higher on goal
difference, only needed to draw.
</P>
<P>
The Germans took an early lead with a backstick field goal by
captain Christian Blunck in the eighth minute, after they missed
their chance in two penalty corners.
</P>
<P>
Spain hit back in the 19th minute with a goal by gutsy forward
Javier Arnau, his seventh in the tournament, to level the score at
halftime.
</P>
<P>
But Germany scored quickly in the second half, with a field
goal from Christoph Eimer and then one from Oliver Domke, aided by
some smart defender-dodging of Philipp Crone.
</P>
<P>
Spain's final goal, in the form of a waist high deflection by
Victor Pujol into the back of the net, was not enough to get it
through.
</P>
<P>
In day's other match, the Netherlands beat Pakistan 5-2 and
will play Spain Saturday for third and fourth places.
</P>
<P>
Also Saturday, Australia, which had already qualified, swamped
the South Korea 6-1 for its fifth straight win in the six-nation
tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
