<HEADLINE> Earthquake Shakes Parepare, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 18 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.0 on
the Richter scale shook Parepare municipality and Pinrang regency
in Indonesia's South Sulawesi province Friday, damaging at least
three houses.
</P>
<P>
People in the two areas, with fresh memories of last month's
earthquake, ran out of their homes, including those who were
attending a wedding party in Pinrang, Antara news agency reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at 8:05 p.m. local time, claimed no
lives.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman for the local meteorological and geophysics office
Kodori said the quake's epicenter was located 40 kilometers
beneath the earth's surface in Polmas district, south of Parepare.
</P>
<P>
An earthquake measuring 6.0 on the Richter scale rocked Sidrap
and Pinrang regencies and Parepare municipality on September 28,
killing 18 people and damaging hundreds of houses.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the last month's quake was located in Pinrang
regency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
