<HEADLINE> 30,000 Nigerians Face Deportation from Saudi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 18 (Xinhua) -- About 30,000 Nigerians living in
Saudi Arabia illegally will be deported in the next one month,
the New Nigerian reported today.
</P>
<P>
The official newspaper said the first batch of 300 deportees
had arrived in Kano City aboard a Nigerian Airways DC 10 airplane
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi Arabian government has given Friday as the deadline
for all illegal immigrants to leave the country. The newspaper
said about 700,000 people, mainly Asians and Africans are to be
affected by the practice.
</P>
<P>
According to the newspaper, the Saudi government has hired the
Nigerian Airways and the Saudi airlines to lift the 30,000
Nigerians. 
