<DOCNO> XIE19971018.0117 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-18 10:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seminar on Regional Economy Opens in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 18 (Xinhua) -- A seminar on economic
development and cooperation in Arab countries, Iran and Turkey
opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The three-day seminar, jointly sponsored by the Kuwait
University, the Kuwait Institute for Scientific Research and the
Economic Research Forum for the Arab Countries, Iran and Turkey
(ERF), was attended by about 40 experts and scholars from the ERF
region, the United States, France, Canada and Senegal.
</P>
<P>
Yousef H. Al-Ebraheem, chairman of the organizing committee and
Dean of College of Administrative Sciences of the Kuwait
University, said in his inaugural speech that the conference is
aimed at strengthening internal cooperation among Arab countries,
Iran and Turkey in the face of challenges of globalization.
</P>
<P>
During the conference on the theme of "Globalization:
Challenges and Opportunities for Development in the ERF Region,"
five main issues including the private sector, trade and
deregulation, regional integration, human resources and
information technology will be discussed and 15 papers would be
presented and debated.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwait-based ERF, founded in 1993 as a non-governmental
and non-profit organization, is aimed at promoting independent
and objective analysis and public discussion of major economic
issues facing the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
