<HEADLINE> Handover of Black Sea Fleet Going Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The vessels and onshore facilities
of the former Soviet Union Black Sea Fleet have been "practically"
transferred to Ukraine, said Naval Commander Mikhail Yezhel today.
</P>
<P>
So far, Russia has turned over 52 naval vessels including 12
warships and 99 facilities to the Ukrainian Navy. However, they
need to undergo repair and maintenance work, Yezhel noted.
</P>
<P>
Russia and Ukraine signed three agreements on the division of
the Black Sea Fleet on May 29, when Russian President Boris
Yeltsin paid a long-delayed visit to Ukraine.  
