<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Commission Supports Romania to Join the Bloc </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC)
will help Romania join the European Union (EU), a senior official
of the regional alliance said here today.
</P>
<P>
The EU's planned eastward expansion to include countries like
Romania is part of a historical process, said Hans Van Den Broek,
deputy president of the EC, the executive arm of the EU.
</P>
<P>
Van Den Broek made the remarks at a press conference after
meeting Romanian President Emil Constantinescu, Prime Minister
Victor Ciorbea and Foreign Minister Adrian Severin.
</P>
<P>
During talks with his hosts, said the EU official in charge of
East and Central European affairs, he called for speeding up
Romania's economic reforms to meet EU membership requirements.
</P>
<P>
The report "Agenda 2000," approved in July by the EC, doesn't
mean granting EU memberships to Romania, Hungary and the Czech
Republic in the first year of the next century, he said.
</P>
<P>
Instead, Van Den Broek told reporters, with the Romanian
foreign minister on his side, that the EU expansion is much of a
job likely to take seven to 10 years on the negotiation table.
</P>
<P>
Romania's formal request for an EU membership was submitted by
Foreign Minister Adrian Severin on June 22, 1995, after the
country was granted the status as an EU associate member. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971018.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coca Cola Expects Full-Scale Growth in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Although most Chinese people
know Coca Cola, few know that the juice marked with "Tianyudi" is
also the product of Coca Cola company.
</P>
<P>
Actually, "Tianyudi" is Coca Cola's first local brand in China.
</P>
<P>
"The birth of the brand demonstrated that Coca Cola has
successfully transferred to China the world's most advanced
technology of soft drink making, and the company began to produce
drinks for the taste of Chinese consumers," said Steve Chan,
general manager of Coca Cola China.
</P>
<P>
Coca Cola has set up a special department to make research on
China market in order to develop beverage for Chinese
people. Canned Tea and soya-bean milk are the focus of the
department's research at present.
</P>
<P>
To make local brand products not only meet the demands of the
Chinese consumers and the diversified soft drink market of China,
but also demonstrated Coca Cola's resolve to continue cooperation
with the Chinese government and further develop in the country,
Chen said.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua prior to Chinese President Jiang
Zemin's upcoming US visit, Chen said that the favorable
development trend of the Sino-US ties in recent years is what the
businesses communities of the two countries have expected, and
what Coca Cola has been working for.
</P>
<P>
The sound bilateral ties is the reason why Coca Cola is
confident of the China market, Chen said, adding that the
development strategy the Chinese government has drafted up made
the company feel that the future of China will be more stable and
it will develop more rapidly.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year development of Coca Cola in China also has made
Chen believe that Coca Cola will enjoy rapid development in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Coca Cola resumed its production in China in 1979, and
established its first bottler in Beijing two years later. Now,
there are 18 Coca Cola bottlers in China with total investment of
over 500 million US dollars. Its products occupied 26 percent of
of the China market. By the end of this year, Coca Cola will have
23 bottlers in China's 21 provinces and cities.
</P>
<P>
What made Chen proud of is that the development of Coca Cola in
China has always linked with the technological upgrading of
China's backward factories. Among its 23 bottlers, there are many
joint ventures between Coca Cola and obsolete state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
While developing in China's coastal region, Coca Cola also pays
attention to central and west China. It has opened office in
Wuhan, capital of central China's Hubei Province, and established
bottlers in eight cities in central and west China.
</P>
<P>
Since the localization rate of Coca Cola's Chinese bottlers has
reached 98 percent, the company will purchase materials and
resources valued at three billion yuan RMB in China each year. The
move has stimulated the development of relevant industries in
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
