<HEADLINE> Angolan, Namibian Police to Step up Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 18 (Xinhua) -- The police authorities of
Angola and Namibia have decided to strengthen cooperation between
them to guarantee security in the border areas of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made by the two sides in the capital of
Angola on Friday at the end of a four-day police meeting.
</P>
<P>
They decided to carry out an operation of fighting cattle
rustling and car stealing in the border areas between Angola and
Namibia soon.
</P>
<P>
The police authorities of the two countries also agreed to
take measures to curb and prevent other criminal activities and
exchange information regularly to eradicate crimes such as drug
and weapons trafficking, illegal exploitation of forest resources
and so on.
</P>
<P>
Angola's Police Commander-in-chief Fernando dos Santos said
that with the crime rate increasing in the border areas,
bilateral police cooperation and exchange of information should
be beefed up to make progress in fighting against criminals.
</P>
<P>
The good relations between the two countries will enable their
policemen to cooperate to reduce the crime rate. 
</P>
