<HEADLINE> Japan Offers ASEAN New Programs for Economic  Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 18 (Xinhua) - Japan today offered ASEAN a
new package of economic programs at the sixth consultation meeting
between ASEAN Economic Ministers(AEM) and Japanese Ministry of
International Trade and Industry(MITI).
</P>
<P>
The new package included some assistance for export companies
and human resources development, according to a statement issued
at the end of the consultation meeting in Subang Jaya near here.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming Japan's offer, the ASEAN ministers reiterated the
programs required further study and emphasized that there should
be prioritizing of work programs in order to make the MITI-ASEAN
initiatives practical and effective.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed that future cooperation should concentrate on
greater integration on trade and investment, improvement of
ASEAN's competitiveness and development cooperation assistance to
new member countries in ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
They felt that the economic fundamentals of ASEAN remained
strong and what was needed was to build on these fundamentals by
improving the competitive ability through improvements in
productivity and infrastructure facilities.
</P>
<P>
To enhance the cooperation activities, the ministers considered
a number of ASEAN's proposals, including projects for the
modernization of ASEAN small and medium enterprises (SMEs), export
promotion, rural industrialization and assistance to the Regional
Network of Statistical Offices.
</P>
<P>
The next AEM-MITI Consultation meeting will be held in October
next year in the Philippines. 
</P>
