<HEADLINE> S. Africa Trains Top Class Prosecutors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 18 (Xinhua) -- A total of 100 prospective
prosecutors were being trained at magistrate's offices throughout
South Africa, the Department of Justice said at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The department said in a statement that the program, which was
being funded with donor money, began in July this year.
</P>
<P>
Candidates had so far been trained in criminal law, criminal
procedure, and laws concerning evidence at magistrate's office in
12 cities, including Cape Town, Durban, Bloemfontein and Port
Elizabeth.
</P>
<P>
They would undergo theoretical training at the Justice College
in Pretoria to augment the practical courses already completed,
the statement said. 
