<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, October 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA -- Cuba buried Friday the legendary Argentine-born Cuban
guerrilla leader Ernesto "Che" Guevara 30 years after he was
killed trying to start revolution in Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
With President Fidel Castro's presence, the funeral took place
in the Revolution Square of the central city of Santa Clara, where
Guevara's remains were buried in a specially built mausoleum.
</P>
<P>
Castro praised the man, his lieutenant in the struggle leading
to Cuba's 1959 revolution, as a moral giant in his tribute.
</P>
<P>
The image of Guevara, the president said, would grow as the
world was blighted with injustice, exploitation, inequality,
unemployment, poverty, hunger and misery. (Cuba-Guevara-Funeral)
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- U.S. Under Secretary of State for Political
Affairs Thomas Pickering will arrive here on Sunday for a two-day
visit to Pakistan, Foreign Office sources said.
</P>
<P>
Pickering is scheduled to meet Pakistani highups to discuss
wide-range issues of bilateral, regional and international
interests, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
His visit will be the first in a series of visits by U.S.
high-level officials to mark Pakistan's 50th anniversary of
independence, with Secretary of State Madeleine Albright expected
to follow in late November and President Bill Clinton early next
year, the sources said. (Pakistan-US-Visit)
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- U.S. President Bill Clinton Friday praised the
South Common Market (Mercosur) and again raised the need to forge
a hemispheric free trade alliance.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting here with 500 Argentine businessmen, the visiting
U.S. president said Mercosur not only helps expand trade in the
region, but also enhances efforts to promote democracy and peace.
(Argentina-US-Free Trade)
</P>
<P>
SHANGHAI -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin, meeting Saturday
with US Senator Orrin Hatch, chairman of the Senate Judiciary
Committee, said that he is looking forward to holding talks with
US President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
Citing his forthcoming state visit to the United States as a
major event in the Sino-US relationship, President Jiang said he
hopes that this visit will enable himself to extensively contact
US congressmen and friends in other sectors, in order to enhance
mutual understanding and friendship between the people of the two
countries. (China-Jiang-US-Meeting)
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Choking smog caused by forest fires in Indonesia
returned to several cities on Friday, and the visibility in one
Sumatra town was reported to be reduced to zero.
</P>
<P>
Government officials said here Saturday visibility in several
cities on Sumatra and Kalimantan islands, was between 100 meters
and 500 meters, and more fires were reported on the two islands.
</P>
<P>
Dense smokes from fires on Sumatra and Borneo have spread over
much of Southeast Asia in the past two months, causing widespread
health warnings and being blamed at least partly for an air crash
and ship collisions. (Indonesia-Smog) 
</P>
</TEXT>
