<HEADLINE> Li Xuemei Runs World's Year-best Time in Women's 100m </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Li Xuemei set the Asian
women's 100 meters record with the year's world best performance
at the Chinese Eighth National Games here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese runner clocked 10.79 seconds, surpassing the
previous year-best time of 10.83 seconds set by world champion
Marion Jones of the United States at the World Athletics
Championships on August 3 in Athens.
</P>
<P>
Li came in 10.90 seconds in the heats on Friday, beating the
previous Asian record of 11.02 established by compatriot Liu
Xiaomei in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The current world record of 10.49 seconds is set by Florence
Griffith Joyner of the United States in 1988. 
