<HEADLINE> Quartey Retains WBA Welterweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 18 (Xinhua) -- World Boxing Association
(WBA) welterweight champion Ike Quartey of Ghana beat the Mexican
challenger Jose Luis Lopez on a majority decision in Ledyard,
Connecticut, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Quartey defended his title for the eighth time and improved to
35-0.
</P>
<P>
Quartey dominated the early action using his jabs, but he was
knocked down 40 seconds into the second round by a wild right from
the Mexican.
</P>
<P>
He survived the knockdown and continued to amass a nearly
insurmountable lead through nine rounds.
</P>
<P>
Lopez came back to drop Quartey for a second time 40 seconds
into the 11th round with an overhand right followed by a left.
</P>
<P>
Quartey came to his feet immediately and protected his lead by
running in the final round and a half.
</P>
<P>
One judge scored the bout even, 113-113, while the other two
awarded the victory to Quartey by scores of 115-114 and 116-112.
</P>
</TEXT>
