<HEADLINE> Pak FM Leaves for Abu Dhabi to Attend Joint Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Foreign Minister
Gohar Ayub Khan left here today for Abu Dhabi, capital of United
Arab Emirates, to lead Pakistan delegation at the 8th Session of
the Pak-UAE Joint Ministerial Commission (JMC), officials said.
</P>
<P>
Gohar was accompanied by a seven-member delegation of senior
officials from the Board of Investment, Foreign Office and other
ministries, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day JMC meeting, Pakistan and UAE will focus on
trade, industrial cooperation and investment in joint ventures,
they said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will also review progress regarding the
implementation of the understandings reached at the 7th JMC
Session, held in Islamabad in November 1995, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Since then both sides have entered an agreement on Reciprocal
Promotion and Protection of Investment which is likely to have a
positive impact on economic relations between the two countries,
they said.  
