<HEADLINE> India, US Agree to Extend Tourist Visa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 18 (Xinhua)-- India and the United States
have reached an agreement on extension of tourist visa span to 10
years from November 1, this year, official sources said here
today.
</P>
<P>
"This measure is in recognition of growing number of visitors
and in preparation for the anticipated growth in tourist and
commercial travel between the two countries," they said.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached here on Friday in the talks between
visiting Under Secretary of State Thomas Pickering, who arrived
here Thursday evening on a two-day visit to India, and Indian
senior officials in the External Affairs Ministry. Pickering held
two rounds of comprehensive talks with Indian Foreign Secretary K.
Raghunath and also met Indian Finance Minister P. Chidambaram here
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The new agreement is expected to greatly facilitate travel by
concerned categories of visitors between the two countries, the
same sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
