<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With US Senators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
meeting today with US Senator Orrin Hatch, chairman of the Senate
Judiciary Committee, said that he is looking forward to holding
talks with US President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
Citing his forthcoming state visit to the United States as a
major event in the Sino-US relationship, President Jiang said he
hopes that this visit will enable himself to extensively contact
US congressmen and friends in other sectors, in order to enhance
mutual understanding and friendship between the people of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that the two countries should approach their
relations from strategic and long-term perspectives, and that they
should pay close attention to the general situation of bilateral
relations, so as to bring bilateral relations to a new period of
development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang extended a welcome to Hatch, and expressed his
appreciation for Hatch's efforts in many years to improve
bilateral ties and support unconditional renewal of the Most
Favored Nation (MFN) trading status to China.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that Chairman Hatch will continue to play
a positive and constructive role in promoting the sound and stable
development of Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
Hatch spoke highly of President Jiang's impending US trip,
saying that the US President, Congress, and the American people
place great importance on the visit, and are ready to extend a
red-carpet welcome to President Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He said they also hope that this visit will further advance
US-China relationship.
</P>
<P>
Hatch and his party are here at the invitation of the Chinese
People's Institute of Foreign Affairs. 
</P>
