<HEADLINE> Forum Centers on Protection of Name-Brand Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Protecting and developing
well-known name-brand products is the central issue on a forum on
quality control opened here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Today's China Daily reported that about 200 high-ranking
officials, outstanding economists and researchers, and
representatives of well-known Chines manufacturers attending the
forum agree that that an economy without name brands lacks
competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
They called for efforts to punish the illegal making and
selling of fake products.
</P>
<P>
In a written congratulatory message to the forum, Vice-Premier
Wu Bangguo said although the quality of Chinese products is good
in general, some serious problems still exist, especially the
practice of making counterfeits of Chinese name-brand products.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the practice has affected the reputations of the
name-brand products of excellent quality, endangered the survival
and development of some enterprises and seriously compromised the
public trust, as well.
</P>
<P>
"It is the common responsibility of the society to crack down
on fake goods and protect well-known brands," Wu stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
