<HEADLINE> Italian PM to Visit Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Italian Prime Minister Romano
Prodi will arrived here Monday for two-day state visit to
strengthen bilateral ties with Indonesia, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
Prodi, who lead a 80-member delegation including high-ranking
officials and prominent business delegates, will discuss with
President Soeharto during his visit various kinds of bilateral
regional and international issues relevant to mutual interests,
Minister/ State Secretary Moerdiono said here last night.
</P>
<P>
"Given Italy's position within the European Union and
Indonesia's position in ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian
Nations), it is hoped that a close relationship between the two
countries will contribute to a more harmonious relationship
between the two regional groups," Moerdiono said.
</P>
<P>
Italy is also a member of Consultative Group on Indonesia, a
group of 18 developed countries which pledged annual loan
commitments to Indonesia. Italy pledged 6.5 million U.S. dollars
out of 5.26 billion U.S. dollars of the group's loan commitments
this year.
</P>
<P>
Italian Ambassador in Indonesia Mario Brando Pensa said here
Friday that Prodi's visit also aimed to strengthen "political
connections" between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Prodi will attend a business luncheon
organized by the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry and
will also attend a dialog and seminar organized by the agency for
the assessment and application of technology, sources here said.
</P>
