<HEADLINE> Triple Champion Chen Yan Eliminated in Backstroke Heats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Chen Yan, who broke the
15-year-old world record in the women's 400m individual medley on
Monday, was eliminated in the heats of the 200 backstroke here
Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
Chen, who has accumulated three gold medals in the first four
days of the National Games, finished last in the Group Three
competition with a time of 2:25:88.
</P>
<P>
However, her dream to win a fourth gold remains alive since she
will take part in the women's 800m freestyle finals tonight.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's Tao Xuan clocked the fastest time of 2:14.28 in the
heats.
</P>
<P>
Zhen Yingjuan, gold winner in the 100m backstroke on Wednesday
with the year's best time, finished second with 2:15.10, with 100m
backstroke world record holder He Cihong at third in 2:15.31.
</P>
<P>
The women's 200m backstroke world mark of 2:06.62 was set by
Hungarian Kristina Egerszegi in Athens on August 25, 1991. 
</P>
