<HEADLINE> Czech Police Seize 60 Kilograms of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Police of the Czech Republic
have seized 60 kilograms of cocaine in the eastern city of Opocno,
the largest drug case cracked in recent years.
</P>
<P>
A 60-year-old Colombian national was arrested. He will face a
sentence of 15 years in prison under Czech law, Police Spokeswoman
Ivana Moosova told reporters today.
</P>
<P>
Anti-drug police and rapid reaction forces discovered the drug,
with a street value of some 3.64 million U.S. dollars, in a truck
near Opocno's railway station on Sunday, Moosova said. 
