<HEADLINE> Japan Supports Bangladesh in seeking Funds for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Japan has expressed its readiness
to support Bangladesh in organizing an international conference
here early next year to galvanize assistance for the construction
of The Ganges barrage project, the national news agency BSS
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The assurance of support was given Thursday in Tokyo during a
meeting between the visiting Bangladeshi Water Resources Minister
Abdur Razzak and Japanese parliamentary Vice-Minister Takeo
Kawamura, BSS quoted a message received Friday as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese vice-minister also assured the Bangladesh minister
that Japan would extend all possible assistance for holding the
conference.
</P>
<P>
In view of the magnitude and size of the project, support of
other donors and agencies would be needed, the Japanese
vice-minister said.
</P>
<P>
The Ganges barrage project, when implemented, would save 40
million people of southwestern Bangladesh from the impending
environmental and ecological disaster, BSS said.
</P>
<P>
The feasibility study for the project is estimated to cost
about 17 million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
