<HEADLINE> Jansher Khan Wins Egyptian Open Squash Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 17 (Xinhua) -- World number one Jansher Khan of
Pakistan overpowered fourth seed Jonathon Power of Canada in three
straight games to Win Egyptian Open Squash Title in Alexandria,
Egypt on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The top seed Jansher khan took the first game 15-5 in only 11
minutes. The Pakistani came from behind 9-6 to take a 12-9 lead
and won the second 15-11 after two backhand drops.
</P>
<P>
Khan then won the third game 15-7 in under 11 minutes and the
tournament title. 
</P>
