<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Has Four Quality Accreditation Agencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 18 (Xinhua) -- China has established four
agencies for quality accreditation to assist export and improve
enterprise management, according to a report in today's China
Daily.
</P>
<P>
The agencies offer accreditation based on the international
specifications and standards set out by the China State Bureau of
Technical Supervision.
</P>
<P>
They are China National Accreditation Council for Registrars
(CNACR), China National Council for Product Quality Certification
Bodies (CNCPQC), China Registration Body for Assessors and the
China National Accreditation Council for Laboratories.
</P>
<P>
CNACR and CNCPQC have joined the International Accreditation
Forum (IAF), an international organization for the world's
accreditation bodies, as well as the Pacific Accreditation Corp,
an organization for accreditation bodies in the Pan-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The ISO9000 quality system certificates issued by CNACR have
gained world recognition since it passed the global
Peer-Evaluation of IAF.
</P>
<P>
CNACR has been authorized to accredit foreign quality system
registration bodies including those in Britain, France, Germany
and Japan.
</P>
<P>
To date, 2,564 enterprises in China have obtained 2,607 quality
system registration certificates, and products of 6,355
enterprises have won 22,552 certification certificates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
