<HEADLINE> Panamanian Police Seize 542 Kilograms of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Panamanian anti-drug police
seized 542 kilograms of cocaine and detained seven persons in two
operations today in the Atlantic coast, according to a police
report.
</P>
<P>
Police agents seized 173 kilograms of the drug hidden in 25 air
conditioning appliances in the Alcazar Internacional company
installations in the Colon Customs Free Zone as it was loaded in a
container for shipment to a South American country.
</P>
<P>
The authorities said that seven persons were detained and the
manager of the company is under investigation.
</P>
<P>
The other 369 kilograms of cocaine was seized during an intense
chase in the Portobelo road of the Atlantic Colon province, after
a suspected truck overturned in the Las Mercedes curve during the
flight toward the city of Colon, some 80 kilometers west of this
capital.
</P>
<P>
Drug trafficking continues being a prime concern for Panamanian
authorities, which have confiscated in less than a week 2,170
kilograms of cocaine.
</P>
<P>
Panama enjoys a perfect geographical position with coasts in
the Atlantic and the Pacific and its neighborhood with Colombia,
which facilitates the transport of drugs toward United States and
European markets.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, Panamanian authorities have confiscated more
than eight tons of cocaine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
