<HEADLINE> Costa Rican President Leaves for U.S. Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rican President Jose
Maria Figueres left here today for New York on a three-day visit
to the United States.
</P>
<P>
Figueres, a former West Point student, will make a visit to his
alma mater during his stay in the United States, the Presidential
House announced.
</P>
<P>
Figueres' current trip to the United States had not been
announced previously.
</P>
<P>
"The invitation extended to Figueres to visit West Point
answers the interest of the institution to know about the efforts
made by Costa Rica to consolidate its political stability and
social peace," Costa Rican Information Minister Alejandro Soto
said.
</P>
<P>
Figueres' West Point education background was a controversial
theme in the last electoral campaign when he was accused of having
a militarist leaning. 
