<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Gets Berth in Semi-finals at Lyon Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Yevgeny
Kafelnikov of Russia stopped Germany's Marc-Kevin Goellner 6-4,
7-5 on Friday, advancing to the semi-finals of the ATP Tour event
in Lyon.
</P>
<P>
The world number seven Kafelnikov, came through comfortably
enough against his world 61-ranked counterpart in the 75-minute
match, who had upset Britain's Tim Henman in the previous round.
</P>
<P>
The second-seeded Russian next plays fast-rising German star
Tommy Haas, 67th in the rankings, who earlier upset fifth-seeded
Swede Thomas Enqvist 6-3, 6-3 to take a place in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Unseeded Frenchman Fabrice Santoro, 42nd in the world rankings,
followed up his victory over former Wimbledon champion Richard
Krajicek on Thursday night with a 6-1, 6-1 win over Spaniard Felix
Mantilla on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Santoro will now face big-serving Australian seventh seed Mark
Philippoussis, who ousted another Frenchman Cedric Pioline 6-3,
3-6, 7-6 (7-4).  
</P>
</TEXT>
