<HEADLINE> South China City Opens Digital Mobile Phone Exchanging Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, October 18 (Xinhua) -- Mobile phone users in Meizhou
in south China's Guangdong Province now can conveniently make
clear calls thanks to the establishment of base stations for the
improvement of local mobile phone communication.
</P>
<P>
The is a great change compared with the past, when all the
local mobile phones could only be got through by exchanging
centers in nearby Shantou city.
</P>
<P>
GSM mobile phone service was provided in Meizhou in 1996. And
the city now has nearly 10,000 GSM mobile phone subscribers.
</P>
<P>
It has spent more than 70 million yuan in importing exchanging
equipment from Sweden for building exchanging centers
locally. Handling capacity of the local digital mobile
communication network has risen to 36,000 lines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
