<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Beats Saudi Arabia to Keep World Cup Hopes Alive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT, October 17 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait revives its World Cup
hopes with a 2-1 victory over Saudi Arabia in a World Cup Asian
Group A qualifier here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Khaled Masaad's 31st-minute penalty pushed Saudi Arabia into
lead. But a red card for Ahmed Jamil in the 40th minute gave the
Kuwaitis a man advantage for the next 45 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Bahar Abdullah's goal two minutes into the second half started
Kuwait's comeback and Jamal Mubarak improved Kuwait to its 2-1
victory in the 68th minute.
</P>
<P>
Fawaz Bakheet also was shown a red card, but not until the 85th
minute.
</P>
<P>
Now Kuwait has seven points with three games left, the same as
Saudi Arabia and China, standing second place on goal difference.
</P>
<P>
Iran stayed atop the group with 11 points by defeating China
4-1 in Tehran earlier Friday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
