<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Raymond Edges Hingis at Zurich Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 17 (Xinhua) -- American Lisa Raymond came from
behind to edge world No.1 Martina Hingis of Switzerland and
entered the semi-finals of the WTA Tour event in Zurich on Friday
night.
</P>
<P>
Raymond overwhelmed the top seed Hingis 4-6, 6-2, 7-5 in a
hard-fought match.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time the Swiss girl had not made at least the
semi-finals of an event since last year's Olympic Games -- 22
tournaments ago.
</P>
<P>
The American, ranked 19th in the world, scored her fourth win
over a top 10 player in the past two weeks.
</P>
<P>
Unseeded Raymond will now play French player Nathalie Tauziat,
who defeated Sabine Appelmans of Belgium 4-6, 6-1, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Jana Novotna of Czech beat compatriot Sandra
Kleinova of 6-2, 7-6 (7-1) on her ninth match point and will meet
fourth-seed Davenport, who won an all-American clash 6-0, 6-4
against prodigy Venus Williams, in the other semi-final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
