<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Dollar Posts Big Gain Against Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 17 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar rose sharply
against other major currencies today, scoring its biggest gain
against the mark since mid-July.
</P>
<P>
In late New York trading, the dollar was quoted at 1.7718
marks, up from 1.7435 late Thursday. The 1.6 percent rise was the
sharpest since July 11. The dollar also was quoted at 120.68 yen,
up from 119.65.
</P>
<P>
Although the dollar is below the eight-year highs of about
1.8800 marks from mid-August, it is higher than its levels at the
start of the year.
</P>
<P>
Against the yen, the dollar rallied late in the session as
negotiators appeared close to a resolution in the dispute that had
led the United States to threaten to bar Japanese cargo ships from
American ports.
</P>
<P>
Other late dollar rates in New York, compared with late
Thursday: 1.4739 Swiss francs, up from 1.4550; 5.9415 French
francs, up from 5.8503; 1,729 Italian lire, up from 1,703; and
1.3862 Canadian dollars, up from 1.3860.
</P>
<P>
The British pound was quoted at 1.6166 U.S. dollars, down from
1.6179 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
